wishlistcomment: Re-implementation of Neue Heimat.  Explore more.

Eurogame; a smooth mix of set collection, push-your-luck and area majority. Players try to collect sets in rummy-style. The trick is that they are allowed to collect a maximum of ten cards before having to play a set and then discarding the rest of their hand to the center display. This display is quickly emptied and not refilled from the draw stack. Thus, drawing blind and hoping for a matching card is a big part of the game. Gamble high unsuccessfully and the game can be lost early on.

comment: I love RoboRally. This has RoboRally guts but is significantly less fun. The 5x5 boards compact the play area too much. The boards have too many elements. Only having 6 dice is too limiting. Getting locked in on moves after taking a second point of damage is too punishing. Rules are poorly written. The ghost ship is a really fun idea but it is too strong since it switches boards to follow you and fires after every bell. It makes it impossible to lower sails and recover damage if you have the treasure since you opponents will use it to destroy you. The most redeeming quality is skulduggery. This game needs a major rules overhaul to be enjoyable. I'd play RoboRally 10 out of 10 times when choosing between the two games.
